# 📘 Enterprise Data Warehouse Pipeline Documentation

**Project Name:** Centralized Part Sales Data Warehouse  
**Cloud Platform:** AWS  
**Core Services:** Amazon S3, AWS Glue, Amazon Redshift, Amazon EventBridge  
**Design Pattern:** Lake‑to‑Warehouse with SCD Management

***

## 1. Project Objective

The objective of this project is to design and implement a **scalable, enterprise‑level data pipeline** that ingests sales data from multiple agencies, processes and governs it centrally, and delivers analytics‑ready data using a **star schema** hosted in Amazon Redshift.

The pipeline supports:

*   Daily operational reporting
*   Monthly reconciliation and restatement
*   Historical tracking using **Slowly Changing Dimensions (SCDs)**
*   High‑volume transactional processing

***

## 2. High‑Level Architecture Overview

### Architecture Pattern

**Data Lake → Staging → Data Warehouse**

    Source Agencies
          ↓
    Amazon S3 (Landing Zone)
          ↓
    AWS Glue Crawlers
          ↓
    AWS Glue Workflows (Multiple Jobs)
     ┌────────────────────────────────────────────┐
     │ Validation | SCD Processing | Staging       │
     │ Fact Consolidation | Load | Quality Checks  │
     └────────────────────────────────────────────┘
          ↓
    Amazon Redshift (Predefined Star Schema)

***

## 3. Data Lake Architecture (Amazon S3)

### 3.1 S3 Zone Design

```text
s3://cdw-part-sales/
├── landing/              ← Raw, immutable
│   └── agency_id=XX/
│       └── load_date=YYYY-MM-DD/
│
├── staging/              ← Cleaned & conformed
│   ├── dim_geography/
│   ├── dim_customer/
│   ├── dim_vendor/
│   ├── dim_part/
│   ├── bridge_vendor_part/
│   └── sales/
│
├── rejected/             ← Data quality failures
├── audit/                ← Load metrics & counts
└── archive/              ← Historical retention
```

### Key Principles

*   **Landing = Raw truth**
*   **Staging = Clean & reusable**
*   **Fact data is NOT stored in S3**

***

## 4. Dimension Classification & SCD Strategy

| Table / Entity  | SCD Type  | Description                 |
| --------------- | --------- | --------------------------- |
| Geography       | Type 1    | Overwrites history          |
| Customer        | Type 1    | Overwrites history          |
| Vendors         | Type 2    | Preserves change history    |
| Vendor\_Parts   | Type 2    | Tracks availability history |
| Parts           | Reference | Static lookup               |
| Sales (staging) | N/A       | Transactional staging only  |
| Fact Table      | N/A       | Stored only in Redshift     |

