## 12. Final Executive / Interview Summary

> This project implements an enterprise‑grade data warehouse pipeline using AWS‑native services and a lake‑to‑warehouse architecture. Raw data lands in Amazon S3 and is processed through AWS Glue workflows that orchestrate validation, SCD‑aware dimension processing, and transactional staging. Type‑1 dimensions overwrite history, Type‑2 dimensions preserve versioned changes, and reference data is refreshed as required. Clean sales data is staged in S3, while the fact table is consolidated within Glue and loaded directly into Amazon Redshift, ensuring optimal performance and single‑source‑of‑truth analytics. The pipeline supports daily incremental loads, monthly reconciliation, and on‑demand processing, delivering scalable, governed, and analytics‑ready data.

